# Cursor AI Rules for this Project

## Code Style
- Write clean, production-quality code
- Follow DRY (Don't Repeat Yourself) principles
- Keep imports at the top of files - never in the middle unless absolutely necessary
- Minimize comments - let the code speak for itself
- Use clear variable and function names instead of explanatory comments
- Write minimal, focused tests - avoid extensive test suites unless essential

## Documentation
- Keep documentation minimal and only when essential

## Implementation
- Implement code directly without extensive documentation
- Focus on code quality over explanation

## File Creation
- Only create files that are functionally necessary
- Avoid helper/explanation markdown files
- Avoid example scripts unless specifically requested

## Communication
- Be concise in responses

